Premier League stars including Steven Gerrard and Theo Walcott plugged an Adidas sale on Twitter . 
  Manchester City's David Silva and Everton's Phil Jagielka were sponsored by the firm . 
  They urged millions of followers to buy the knock-down goods for 25 hours . 
  Players posted messages within minutes of each other yesterday . 
  Comes amid concern celebrities are cashing in by turning Twitter into an advertising platform . 
  Advertising Standards Authority has not yet received any complaints . 
 